quizzes.question:
Turn the text into a comment in CSS:
[!raw!]
{0} This is a comment {1}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Comments[/h1]

Comments are used to explain your code, and may help you when you edit the source code later. Comments are ignored by browsers.

A CSS comment look like this: [code format="css" ]/* Comment goes here */[/code]
[b]Example: [/b] [code format="css" codeId="507"]p { 
  color: green; 
  /* This is a comment */
  font-size: 150%;
}[/code]
The comment does not appear in the browser: [img id="2587" width="100%"]
[note]Comments can also span multiple lines.[/note]
